data.value:
Dynamics
1) v = u + at 2) s = ut + 0.5at^2 3) v^2 = u^2 + 2as 4) Force = mass * acceleration 5) Force = momentum change / time 6) Weight = mass * gravity 7) Momentum = mass * velocity 8) Work done = Force * displacement 9) Work done = FcosA * displacement 10) Power = work done / time taken 11) Kinetic energy = 0.5 * mass * velocity^2 12) G.P.E = mass * gravitation * height
Circular Motion
13) Period (T) = 2 * Pi / Angular velocity 14) Speed = radius of circle * angular velocity 15) Acceleration = velocity^2 / radius of circle 16) Acceleration = radius of circle * angular velocity^2
Gravitation
17) T^2 = r^3(Newton's law of gravitation) 18) Gravitational Force = G m*M / r^2 19) Density of a planet = 3 * g / 4 * pi * radius* G 20) Mass of planet = g * r^2 / G 21) Period of satellite in its orbit = sqroot(4 * Pi^2 * R^3 / g * r^2) 22) Velocity of escape = sqroot(2 * g * r)
Simple Harmonic Motion
23) Acceleration = -Angular velocity^2 * y 24) Maximum velocity = Angular velocity * radius of circle 25) Velocity at any instant = angular velocity * sqroot(radius^2 - Distance^2)
Molecules and matter, Elasticity
26) Tensile stress = Force / area 27) Tensile strain = extension / length 28) Young modulus of elasticity(E) = Tensile stress / Tensile strain 29) Energy stored in a wire = 0.5 * Force * extension 30) Energy stored in a wire = 0.5 * E * A * extension^2 / Length
Temperature
31) Temperature(Kelvin's) = 273 + Degrees Celsius Temperature 32) Specific heat capacity = mass * Specific heat capacity * Temp change 33) Ideal Gas equation: pV = nRT 34) Pressure= Force / area 35) Pressure = density * gravity * depth 36) Pressure = 1/3 * number of molecules * mass * R.M.S speed 37) R.M.S = sqroot(3 * R * T / M) 38) Boltzmann constant(k) = (0.5 * m * R.M.S^2) / (3/2T) 39) Monatomic Internal Energy = 3/2 * R * T 40) Diatomic Internal Energy = 5/2 * R * T 41) Linear Expansitivity = Expansion / Original length * Temperature rise 42) Cubic Expansitivity = Increase in Volume / Original volume * Temp rise
Geometrical Optics
43) Lateral Magnification(m) = height of image / height of object 44) Ref index of light in materials= Vel of light in vacuum/ Vel of light in medium 45) Absolute Ref Index = Sin(i) / Sin(r) 46) Angular Magnification(M) = diameter of objective / diameter of eye ring 47) Power of a lens = 1 / focal length of lens
Waves, wave Optics and Sound
48) Wave velocity(v) = frequency * wavelength 48) Fringe separation = a * y/ D 49) Sin(@) = wavelength / spacing of slits {diffraction images)
Electricity and Atomic physics
50) Permittivity of free space = Charge 1 * Charge 2 / (4 * Pi * Force * r^2) 51) Intensity(E) = Force / charge 52) Work done = Charge * Potential difference 53) Capacitance = Charge / Potential difference 54) Charge = Capacitance * Potential difference 55) Potential difference = Charge / capacitance 56) Electric Voltage = current * resistance 57) Electric Current = Voltage / resistance 58) Electric Resistance = Voltage / current 59) Resistivity = Resistance of wire * Cross-sectional area/ length of wire 60) Electric power = Current * voltage 61) Electric power = Current^2 * resistance 62) Electric power = Voltage^2 / resistance 63) Increase in mass(m) = zIt 64) Force on moving charges(F) = BeV or BQV 65) Magnetic flux linkage = NBA 66) Force on current carrying conductor = BIL 67) Force on electron moving between charged plates = eE or EQ 68) Energy of a photon = Frequency of radiation * velocity of photon = hv 69) Wavelength = Planck's constant / momentum (De Broglie's Theory)
Radioactivity
70) Half-life of an atom = 0.693 / Decay Constant 71) Binding energy = mass difference of nucleons and nucleus * 931MeV 72) Activity(rate of decay) = Decay constant / Number of undecayed nuclei 73) E = mc^2 (Einstein's mass and energy relation)
